    • getUpcoming

      public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> getUpcoming()

      Returns:
      observable list of upcoming appointments

    • getTypes

      observable list of all appointment types

    • add

      public static int add(String title, String desc, String loc, String type, LocalDateTime start, LocalDateTime end, int custId, int userId, int contId)
      Calls to database and inserts new appointment.
      Parameters:
      title - appointment title
      desc - appointment description
      loc - appointment location
      type - appointment type
      start - appointment start time/date, expressed in local timezone
      end - appointment end time/date, expressed in local timezone
      custId - customer ID
      userId - user ID
      contId - contact ID
      Returns:
      new appointment ID if successful, otherwise -1 to indicate failure

    • update

      public static int update(int id, String title, String desc, String loc, String type, LocalDateTime start, LocalDateTime end, int custId, int userId, int contId)
      Calls to database and updates existing appointment by ID.
      Parameters:
      id - existing appointment ID
      title - appointment title
      desc - appointment description
      loc - appointment location
      type - appointment type
      start - appointment start time/date, expressed in local timezone
      end - appointment end time/date, expressed in local timezone
      custId - customer ID
      userId - user ID
      contId - contact ID
      Returns:
      count of rows updated if successful, otherwise -1 to indicate failure

    • delete

      public static int delete(int id)

      Parameters:
      id - ID of appointment to delete
      Returns:
      count of rows deleted if successful, otherwise -1 to indicate failure

    • hasCustomer

      public static boolean hasCustomer(int id)
      Determines if customer has existing appointments in the database. This method calls to the database using the given customer ID, then returns if there were any results.
      Parameters:
      id - existing customer ID
      Returns:
      true if customer has appointments, otherwise false

    • overlaps

      public static boolean overlaps(int customerId, LocalDateTime newStart, LocalDateTime newEnd)
      Determines if given start and end dates/times overlap with existing appointments by customer. This method calls to the database using the given customer ID, then iterates through matching appointments to determine if there are any overlapping dates/times.
      Parameters:
      customerId - existing customer ID
      newStart - desired start date/time, expressed in local timezone
      newEnd - desired end date/time, expressed in local timezone
      Returns:
      true if given start and end dates/times overlap with existing customer appointments, otherwise false

    • overlaps

      public static boolean overlaps(int customerId, LocalDateTime newStart, LocalDateTime newEnd, int apptId)
      Determines if given start and end dates/times overlap with existing appointments by customer, excluding appointment with given ID. This method calls to the database using the given customer ID, then iterates through matching appointments to determine if there are any overlapping dates/times.
      Parameters:
      customerId - existing customer ID
      newStart - desired start date/time, expressed in local timezone
      newEnd - desired end date/time, expressed in local timezone
      apptId - existing appointment ID to exclude from comparison
      Returns:
      true if given start and end dates/times overlap with existing customer appointments, otherwise false

    • getValidTimes

      public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<String> getValidTimes()
      Returns list of times, as strings, during business hours, expressed in local timezone.
      Returns:
      observable list of times in local timezone during business hours, expressed as strings
